ciscoDs0CrossConnectMIB.name: ciscoDs0CrossConnectMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of the MIB module.

ciscoDs0CrossConnectMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-voice@cisco.com
ciscoDs0CrossConnectMIB.description: The MIB for Ds0 cross connection.

cds0CrossConnectConfigTable.name: cds0CrossConnectConfigTable
cds0CrossConnectConfigTable.description: This table is used to establish a DS0 cross connection. A DS0 cross connect is established by binding a unique DS0 group containing one or more DS0s of a single Ds1 interface to another unique DS0 group containing one or more DS0s of a single DS1 interface.

cds0CrossConnectConfigEntry.name: cds0CrossConnectConfigEntry
cds0CrossConnectConfigEntry.description: An entry in cds0CrossConnectConfigTable table represents a DS0 cross connection. The two end point of the connection are: end point 1: cds0Endpt1Ds1 cds0Endpt1Ds0Group end point 2: cds0Endpt2Ds1 cds0Endpt2Ds0Group The end points of this connection should be entries of ccasGrpCfgTable and 'ccasGrpCfgServiceType' of of the entries should be 'tdmxconn'. The ccasGrpCfgTable is defined in CISCO-CAS-IF-MIB.

cds0Endpt1Ds1.name: cds0Endpt1Ds1
cds0Endpt1Ds1.description: The value of this object equals to the 'ifIndex' of a Ds1 interface. This Ds1 interface is used as the first end point of the Ds0 connection.

cds0Endpt1Ds0Group.name: cds0Endpt1Ds0Group
cds0Endpt1Ds0Group.description: The value of this object identifies a Ds0 group which contains one of more Ds0(s) within the Ds1 interface represented by 'cDs0Endpt1Ds1'. This Ds0 group is used as the first end point of the Ds0 connection.

cds0Endpt2Ds1.name: cds0Endpt2Ds1
cds0Endpt2Ds1.description: The value of this object equals to the 'ifIndex' of a Ds1 interface. This Ds1 interface is used as the second end point of the Ds0 connection.

cds0Endpt2Ds0Group.name: cds0Endpt2Ds0Group
cds0Endpt2Ds0Group.description: The value of this object identifies a Ds0 group which contains one of more Ds0(s) within the Ds1 interface represented by 'cDs0Endpt2Ds1'. This Ds0 group is used as the second end point of the Ds0 connection.

cds0ConnRowStatus.name: cds0ConnRowStatus
cds0ConnRowStatus.description: This object is used to create or delete an entry. The mandatory objects for creating an entry in this table: 'cds0Endpt2Ds1' 'cds0Endpt2Ds0Group' The following objects are not allowed to be modified after the entry to be added: 'cds0Endpt2Ds1' 'cds0Endpt2Ds0Group'

ciscoDs0CrossConnectMIBCompliance.name: ciscoDs0CrossConnectMIBCompliance
ciscoDs0CrossConnectMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for Cisco agents which implement the CISCO-DSO-CROSS-CONNECT-MIB.

cDs0CrossConnectConfigGroup.name: cDs0CrossConnectConfigGroup
cDs0CrossConnectConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects for general configuration of Ds0 cross connection.
